page.title: 11ANIMALS
page.content: The woods & copses provide shelter for a wide variety of animal life. Foxes are present in considerable numbers as are badgers,hares & rabbits. Stock of the latter is kept down by the recurrence of myxomatosis from time to time, A few roe deer roam the area doing considerable damage to growing crops in the fields & raiding gardens during hard winter weather.Muntjak have been seen but seldom more than one pair.There are many smaller animals in quite large numbers such as weasels, hedgehogs, rats, water voles, grey squirrels & the occasional coypu. There is evidence of much activity by moles & as the mole catcher is a vanishing breed they continue to multiply.
